<paragraph blockId="3.[236,1352,1476,1575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1108">
C o m m e n t: According to 
<bibRefCitation author="SMETANA A" box="[632,850,1476,1503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1108" pagination="505 - 698" refId="ref14671" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Staphylinidae, subfamilies Omaliinae - Dasycerinae, Phloecharinae - Apaticinae, Piestinae - Staphylininae, pp. 237 - 272, 329 - 495, 505 - 698. - In: LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A. (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. II. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. Stenstrup: Apollo Books, 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, this rarely found species is distributed from the Balkans to the Western Mediterranean, but was previously unknown from 
<collectingCountry box="[236,311,1548,1575]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="1108">Spain</collectingCountry>
. It was only recently reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[757,863,1548,1575]" name="Portugal" pageId="3" pageNumber="1108">Portugal</collectingCountry>
for the first time (
<bibRefCitation author="SILVA P" box="[1092,1312,1548,1575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1108" pagination="397 - 399" refId="ref14608" refString="SILVA P. M. DE, FARIA E SILVA I. DE, BOIEIRO M., AGUIAR C. A. S. &amp; A. R. M. SERRANO (2006): Four new records to the rove-beetle fauna of Portugal (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Boletin Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa 39: 397 - 399." type="journal article" year="2006">SILVA et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
